---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentPage from '../components/ContentPage.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy | Fight Prophet"
  description="Fight Prophet editorial policy for original analysis, sourcing, corrections, model claims, and content quality."
>
  <ContentPage
    eyebrow="Editorial Policy"
    title="Editorial Policy"
    intro="Fight Prophet publishes original model explanations, rankings context, and MMA analytics notes. This policy explains how content is produced and corrected."
    updated="May 17, 2026"
  >
    <section>
      <h2>Original Analysis First</h2>
      <p>
        The public site is designed around original interpretation of Fight Prophet data.
        It does not rely on copied articles, scraped news pages, or automated rewrites of
        other publishers. External sources may be linked when they help verify a fact, but
        Fight Prophet pages should add analysis, methodology, or context of their own.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="fp-content-grid">
      <section>
        <h2>Sourcing</h2>
        <p>
          Data pages may combine structured fight records, public event information, manual
          overrides, and model outputs. When a page discusses a claim that depends on an
          external publisher or official record, the page should link out rather than
          reproduce the source.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Corrections</h2>
        <p>
          Corrections are prioritized when they affect fighter identity, fight result, title
          status, country, activity status, model explanation, privacy, or policy compliance.
          Readers can send corrections through the contact page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Model Claims</h2>
      <p>
        Model outputs must be described as estimates. Fight Prophet avoids language that
        guarantees outcomes, promises profit, or implies sportsbook endorsement. When a
        model is uncertain, the content should say so plainly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="fp-content-note">
      <h2>Advertising Standard</h2>
      <p>
        Ads and support widgets should not overwhelm publisher content, block navigation, or
        make it unclear what belongs to Fight Prophet. The public site keeps policy, privacy,
        contact, and methodology pages reachable from the main navigation and footer.
      </p>
    </section>
  </ContentPage>
</BaseLayout>
